external_knowledge:
- "stands tallest" is a metaphor for having the highest value;
- "warmest" refers to the highest average temperature;
- "judged by the average temperature of its yearly data points" means the region is selected based on the average temperature calculated from multiple years of climate data.

sql:
SELECT MIN(metric_value) AS lowest_temperature
FROM climate_metrics
WHERE metric_name = 'temperature';

SELECT COUNT(data_id)
FROM climate_data
WHERE temp_avg > (SELECT AVG(temp_avg) FROM climate_data);

external_knowledge:
- "Explorers of the digital world" refers to users who access and download climate data from the system;
- "Embarked on more than one journey" means they have accessed more than one data entry;
- "Gather climate data" refers to downloading climate data entries;
- "Discovered a new piece of data" refers to the latest upload date of the data they accessed;
- "Each region they explored" refers to the different regions from which the climate data originates.

- 'halfway point of the recorded climate years' refers to the year ID being greater than the average year ID from the `years` table;
- 'climate years' are the years for which climate data is recorded;
- 'average temperature' is the mean temperature over the specified period.

sql:
SELECT AVG(temp_avg) AS avg_temp
FROM climate_data
WHERE region_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
