- 'Region' refers to geographical areas where climate data is collected;
- The query focuses on the region that has the highest number of climate data entries.

- 'Warmth of the sun' refers to an average temperature above 20 degrees Celsius;
- 'Moisture of the air' refers to an average humidity above 50 percent;
- 'Vast garden of climate data' refers to the comprehensive climate data records stored in the database.
